That makes sense. Though I think then it might make more sense to not use a
callback api at all, but rather, add an "update server ssl credentials" api
that so that users can call when there are actually new credentials,
instead of having the core lib call the callback on every new connection.
And clients would not use this new api , and just create new channel when
they have new credentials.

I guess potential downside is there is potentially slightly more locking
complexity for the server, i.e. a separate thread that "manages/monitors"
the credentials and calls into the core lib when there is new cert.

Thoughts?
